    "Hence, our proof of the localisation given in section 4.3 was indeed valid.",
    "E Comments on factorisationThe goal of this appendix is to explain the factorisation F ∂ΦJ + (z) = F ∂Φ (z)F J + (z) used in section 5.1.",
    "More generally, we will discuss conditions under which a factorisation F AB (z) = F A (z)F B (z) occurs for operators A(z) and B(z).",
    "The conditions we provide will be sufficient for our key example of A = ∂Φ and B = J +, yet it may well be possible to provide less stringent conditions on A and B for the factorisation to hold."
